Charles Manson comes up for parole every so often, it's scary that he could actually get out, if the circumstances were right.<br>
<br>
We have executed innocents, as we have jailed innocents as well.  That's a sad reality, that we will never be able to correct.  <br>
<br>
I agree with the death penalty, but like our legal system in general, the process is the problem. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18533>Sister Maddie Faye</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usapiens1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sapiens1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/7/02 11:27:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Capital Punishment</span><hr size=1> So... how many people here claim that executing an innocent man is acceptable?<br>
